imagine we have a branch like bugfix, and we have a no ff merge (have commit merge)
in this merge, commits on the bugfix branch, will be history of Main branch.
but what if bugfix branch commits (B1,B2) have not good quality,
they are too fine grained! or don't represent a logical step!
they just check point, they will pollute Main history!
and we don't really care about history of bugfix branch.
SOLUTION is "squash merging"!
                                          MAIN
                                           |
                                           v
+------+    +------+    +------+    +-------------+
| C1   |<---| C2   |<---| C3   |<---|merge commit |
+------+    +------+    +------+    +-------------+     Note: this history shows that because of c3
                   ^                   |                      we should have conflict on merge!
                   |                   |
                +------+    +------+   |
                | B1   |<---| B2   |<--+
                +------+    +------+
                               ^
                               |
                              bugfix




SQUASH MERGING
it will aggregate all the commit's on other branch (from deviation point)
and put it on Main branch as a "single commit".

Note: this new commit by squash merging, IS NOT MERGE COMMIT!
      because it does not have two parent. (it does not have pointer to B2)
      it just regular commit added to master.

                                          MAIN
                                           |
                                           v
+------+    +------+    +------+    +-------------+
| C1   |<---| C2   |<---| C3   |<---| B1+B2 commit|
+------+    +------+    +------+    +-------------+    Note: the squash commit has not
                   ^                                         any pointer to B2!
                   |
                +------+    +------+
                | B1   |<---| B2   |
                +------+    +------+
                               ^
                               |
                              bugfix

Note: in best practice, when we used squash merging
      we should delete the other branch (bugfix branch)
      because there is not any pointer on main branch to bugfix branch
      (squash commit has not pointer to the B2 commit)
      git recognize him as unmerged branch. so when we use
      "git branch --no-merged" on main, it show bugfix as unmerged branch!
      so it could create ambiguity for others!
      just delete bugfix branch (B1,B2 will be garbage)

Note: in best practice, we use squash merging on
      short lived branches with bad history
      like a branch for resolving a bug!

